DENGUE/DHF UPDATE 2008 (30): BRAZIL
***********************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

In this update:
[1] Brazil (Rio Grande do Norte)
[2] Brazil (Campos, Rio de Janeiro state)

******
[1] Brazil (Rio Grande do Norte)
Date: Fri 25 Jul 2008
Source: Diario de Natal [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://diariodenatal.dnonline.com.br/site/materia.php?idsec=2&idmat=173611>


Since the beginning of this year [2008] the State Public Health
Department recorded 37 147 suspected cases of dengue in all
municipalities of Rio Grande do Norte. In 1161 [3 percent] of these
cases, DHF [dengue hemorrhagic fever] was suspected, with 206
confirmations up to the present time. The deaths of 63 persons who
showed DHF symptoms were also reported [5 percent case fatality rate],
and laboratory tests confirmed [DHF as] the cause of [of death in] 7
of these cases.

Just in Grande Natal there were 18 453 [dengue cases] reported, of
which 753 were DHF [4 percent]. Also, there are 22 deaths in the
region suspected to have been due to the disease [3 percent case
fatality rate], with [laboratory] confirmation of 2 cases.

There were 9978 dengue fever and 1159 DHF cases [12 percent]
concentrated in the state capital [Natal].

In the west and Vale do Acu, dengue attacked 3429 people, with 50
suspected cases of DHF [1.5 percent]. Just in Mossoro, there were 1535
reported cases of dengue fever, and 13 of DHF [1 percent].
--
